[{"sha":"cd1663813e54f5afe0c265b1ac32ed9a993c82b9","author":{"name":"Martin Atkins","email":"a1bdfbfb01322b54f9edf8cea8f328c9384b211a@degeneration.co.uk"},"message":"getmodules: Beginnings of a new package about Terraform module packages

This new package aims to encapsulate all of our interactions with
go-getter to fetch remote module packages, to ensure that the rest of
Terraform will only use the small subset of go-getter functionality that
our modern module installer uses.

In older versions of Terraform, go-getter was the entire implementation
of module installation, but along the way we found that several aspects of
its design are poor fit for Terraform's needs, and so now we're using it
as just an implementation detail of Terraform's handling of remote module
packages only, hiding it behind this wrapper API which exposes only
the services that our module installer needs.

This new package isn't actually used yet, but in a later commit we will
change all of the other callers to go-getter to only work indirectly
through this package, so that this will be the only package that actually
imports the go-getter packages.","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/terraform/commits/cd1663813e54f5afe0c265b1ac32ed9a993c82b9"},{"sha":"95bbde857b232522e63c8513313b15b837d3be8c","author":{"name":"Martin Atkins","email":"a1bdfbfb01322b54f9edf8cea8f328c9384b211a@degeneration.co.uk"},"message":"addrs: Representation of module source addresses

We've previously had the syntax and representation of module source
addresses pretty sprawled around the codebase and intermingled with other
systems such as the module installer.

I've created a factored-out implementation here with the intention of
enabling some later refactoring to centralize the address parsing as part
of configuration decoding, and thus in turn allow the parsing result to
be seen by other parts of Terraform that interact with configuration
objects, so that they can more robustly handle differences between local
and remote modules, and can present module addresses consistently in the
UI.","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/terraform/commits/95bbde857b232522e63c8513313b15b837d3be8c"},{"sha":"2e4987e19256db41ceb3c213a0429dd6f5ba3497","author":{"name":"Martin Atkins","email":"a1bdfbfb01322b54f9edf8cea8f328c9384b211a@degeneration.co.uk"},"message":"wip new module source address type","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/terraform/commits/2e4987e19256db41ceb3c213a0429dd6f5ba3497"}]

[{"sha":"fb5a9ec741c4a2246624b694d88db2e5fabc9118","author":{"name":"Angel Velazquez","email":"e7be62313d96a6aa5d44f8f6bc3f3eab388c04d9@amazon.com"},"message":"Limit the rate at which logger errors are logged into daemon logs

Logging to daemon logs every time there's an error with a log driver can be
problematic since daemon logs can grow rapidly, potentially exhausting disk
space.

Instead, it's preferable to limit the rate at which log driver errors are allowed
to be written. By default, this limit is 333 entries per second max.

some TF libraries got loaded twice and some global variables got overwritten.

This bug was introduced in de37b1e - TF statically loads a bunch of TF_VARIANT decoders,
but then it dynamically loads the same (or some) libraries and overwrites global lists,
this bug has actually been there forever, but no one uses TF_VARIANT to store bool or int32,
so when those got overwritten (actually, lost), no one cared.

But variant decoder for TensorList got lost and reverting de37b1e should have fixed that.
This patch fixed the bug by explicitly calling single static function defined not in a header, but in C code.

Please see https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/44428 for how
this bug was found and which fix worked for macos, the second commit
will fix it for everyone.","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/39812646c944af98ee9ad1c1ce86eb9d57a1aded"},{"sha":"6d6a1d272c73977dd2a1824adf6aff9644190779","author":{"name":"Evgeniy Polyakov","email":"9be07b15919dab1b45f07f962d8e37ba7c50f920@ioremap.net"},"message":"This bug was introduced in 15275d3 - because TF libs got loaded the
second time somewhere in its life cycle (probably dynamically when there
are multiple saved_model models in the same inference environment,
please see https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/44428 for
examples and fixes), RTTI changes for every class for every new dynamic
library loading, thus TensorList got different RTTI ID and decoder in
variant->get<VariantTensorDataProto>() refuses to decode protobuf.

You have fixed this for MacOS by reverting to the old behaviour (and for
Windows in master branch), now my patch forces this for everyone else.","distinct":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/commits/6d6a1d272c73977dd2a1824adf6aff9644190779"},{"sha":"c0e3912234daea6367d27cbc550ec3d161f2c372","author":{"name":"Gaurav Shukla","email":"a5a4545b386c0b530f3dfc1d9cf67b86bc4f8dab@cerebras.net"},"message":"[MLIR] Add lowering of TF::SoftsignOp
